data.description:
PASSIVE SOLAR 3 BEDROOM, 2 ½ BATH HOME

Passive solar design- No furnace, no AC
Comfortable year round inside
Hydronic radiant wall heat and cooling (supplemental as needed)
Extra-large garage
Walk-in closets in every bedroom
Extra storage space
Root cellar 
Woodburning stove for supplemental heat (rarely needed) with 4” outside air intake
RV parking and hook-up

Established fruit trees (peach, plum, pear, apple, jujube, blackberries)

Sunken greenhouse for year-round food growing

What makes this home a green or healthy home?
This passive solar, maximum R-Value Insulated Concrete Form  (ICF) home requires very little energy to maintain full comfort year-round. South-facing design allows sunlight to heat the home in winter. Roof overhangs stop the sun from hitting windows and walls during summer, and windows provide night-time cooling to maintain daytime cool temperatures in the house. White 40-year metal roof reflects heat out in the summer, minimizing heat gain upstairs. Inside the roof insulation is 10 inch expanded foam for heat stabilization summer and winter. Wood-burning stove and evaporative cooler are available for supplemental heat or cooling, but are seldom needed. Supplemental heating upstairs is also provided by a hydronic radiant wall system heated by a natural gas water heater. In the summer, cool water from 3000 feet of buried water pipe is circulated in the system for supplemental cooling upstairs.

No herbicides used on this property; this home is the first build and use of the property so the ground is chemical free.

Six (6) raised beds for growing food with timed water systems. (Ask for more pictures.) Last year one 30 foot raised bed yielded 200 Lbs. of sweet potatoes.

Fruit trees in a fully fenced back yard to protect from deer include three (3) peach; two (2) purple plum trees, two (2) Santa Rosa plum, one (1) Italian prune; two (2) pear trees; two (2) apple trees; one (1) cherry tree; two (2) apricot trees; one (1) jujube; productive blackberry row; ground cherry and four (4) grape vines produce fruit much of the summer. 

Back yard is fully fenced.  

No-till garden produces a large crop of vegetables.

Front yard includes medicinal and decorative flowers and herbs as well as an English Walnut tree and a Black Walnut tree.  Medicinal herbs in abundance include Mullein, Yarrow, Comfrey, Echinacea, Sage, Peppermint, Spearmint, Catnip, Marshmallow, and Plantain.  

In-ground 48’X 16’ greenhouse with three (3) large raised beds (180 sq ft) and aboveground 8800-gallon pool to manage temperature, summer and winter.  The massive amount of water to balance the temperature means the greenhouse doesn't freeze in the winter and is just a little warmer than outside in the summer.  Yes you can swim in the pool.

Lawn is deep rooted Buffalo grass, low water use and low-maintenance

Home Description:
This ICF home is built to withstand earthquake, fire, or extreme weather events with little or no maintenance. Siding is concrete, and roof is 40-year raised seam metal. No painting needed for exterior.

All three (3) bedrooms are large and have walk-in closets.  Also a bonus room 24x12 over the garage for hobby, exercise or storage.  

This home was designed for a self-reliant lifestyle, including the sunken greenhouse, raised beds, and multiple fruit trees.  The cellar has plenty of room for all your canned fruit and the stairs are right off the kitchen for easy access.  The cellar is also a completely separate structure under the home so is a safe shelter and maintains a constant temperature.  It also has a fresh air tube into one side and out the other side.
The home also includes a spot for RV parking with a 30-amp electric hookup, water, and sewage/tank dump.

In addition to the passive solar greenhouse (16x48) there are outbuildings for chickens, and a tractor shed (20x16) and storage shed (20x10)
data.whatILove: Built as a passive solar home with no AC or Furnace and with supplemental hydronic Heating and Cooling this home is designed to use very little energy. The average utility cost is less than $100 per month. It stays comfortable year-round.  Solar Electric was added in 2023
